3:["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["How Funding Works on ","Paradex"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Paradex calculates funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average of the premium between the perpetual price and underlying spot price. The platform's StarkNet appchain architecture enables efficient computation of funding payments without compromising decentralization. Portfolio margin mechanics allow traders to optimize capital efficiency across multiple positions, while the 0.02% maker fee structure incentives liquidity provision. Funding payments are automatically settled from traders' collateral balances at each hourly interval."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ENA","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ENA's role as a governance token for Ethena Protocol creates periodic demand spikes during governance events and protocol updates, leading to volatile funding rates. The token's synthetic dollar (USDe) backing mechanism introduces additional complexity to price discovery, often resulting in significant premiums or discounts. Mid-tier trading volume on Paradex means funding rates can deviate substantially from larger centralized exchanges, creating cross-venue arbitrage opportunities for traders with sufficient capital."}]]}],[["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"ENA Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ENA funding rates on Paradex typically exhibit higher volatility during Ethena Protocol governance periods and USDe backing ratio adjustments. Historical data shows funding rates ranging from -2% to +4% annually during major protocol events, significantly exceeding the 0.1-0.5% range seen during quiet periods. The token's correlation with broader DeFi sentiment means funding rates often spike during DeFi summer periods or governance token rallies. Paradex's limited ENA trading volume can amplify these movements, with funding rates sometimes remaining elevated for multiple 1-hour cycles before mean reversion."}]]}],["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-venue arbitrage between Paradex and major CEXs like Binance or OKX frequently yields 5-15 basis points per funding period during volatile periods. The self-custodial nature of Paradex means arbitrageurs avoid exchange custody risks while maintaining exposure to funding rate differentials. Portfolio margin capabilities enable capital-efficient hedging strategies, allowing traders to maintain delta-neutral positions while capturing funding rate alpha. Advanced traders can exploit the 1-hour funding frequency to capture intraday rate movements that 8-hour funding exchanges miss."}]]}],"$L8"],"$L9"]}]
